# This script selects 250 most important OTUs via a Mutual Information Maximization criterion. It tests the accuracies and consistencies of the sets of OTUs for set sizes from 50 to 250 by step of 2. The environmental parameter that is being predicted is STATE and it is subclustered according to the -k arguments. -f and -g arguments make sure we select only fecal samples (from the BODY_HABITAT column of the map file) 

python consistency_testing.py -b pathToDataset/AG_100nt.biom -c STATE -k "ME;NH;VT;MA;RI;CT;NY;PA;NJ;DE;MA;DC" -k HI -k AK -k "WV;VA;KY;NC;SC;TN;GA;FL;AL;MS;AR;LA;OK;TX" -k "ND;MN;MI;OH;IN;IL;MO;IA;NE;SD;MT;WY;KS;ID;WI" -k "WA;CA;OR;NV;NM;AZ;UT;CO" -o ./oneloop/americangut-state-cluster/ -j mim -p 50 -q 250 -s 2 -m pathToDataset/AG_100nt.txt -f BODY_HABITAT -g UBERON:feces
